PYTHON: requirements and instructions

Python 3.4 and the following modules:
- gunicorn 19.4.1
- falcon 0.3.0
- requests 2.9.1
- configparser 3.5.0
- jsonschema 2.5.1
- sqlite3 2.6.0
- sqlalchemy 1.0.11
- networkx 1.10

Installations
$ sudo apt-get install python3
$ sudo apt-get install python3-setuptools
$ sudo easy_install3 pip

To install a python3 module:
$ sudo pip3 install <module>

To check if a module is already installed and its version:
$ pip3 freeze



INSTRUCTIONS

1)	Set full permissions on the main directory:
	$ chmod 777 <directory>

2)	Check ./configuration.conf and write your own configuration.
   
